Dividend Brief -- Geico Corp.:
   Board Declares 5-for-1 Split
   And 31% Dividend Increase
Geico is a property and casualty insurer, particularly for
private automobiles. The split is subject to stockholder
approval of an increase in the number of Geico's authorized
common shares to 150 million from 60 million. A vote on the
authorized share total will be taken at Geico's annual
meeting May 20, and the split is expected to take effect
shortly afterward if the increase is approved.
   The dividend increase, to 75 cents a share from 57 cents,
is payable March 31 to shares of record March 9.